## Early game

Neurodes have a very low chance to drop from regular enemies, so the wiki's own
advice is to hunt containers instead of grinding kills. **Mantle** on Earth
(Capture) runs through the Grineer cave tileset, where the green-glowing
resource containers reliably carry Neurodes — a short Capture that's easy to
repeat without needing a boss fight or an endless mission. Because it's a
container pickup, Resource Drop Boosters and the Steel Path drop-chance passive
don't apply here, so there's no rush to save the farm for later. Other Earth
nodes with the same Grineer caves (**Mariana** Exterminate, **Tikal**
Excavation) work as secondary stops.

If you'd rather fight for them, **Magnacidium** on Deimos (Assassination,
Lephantis) is one of the easiest boss-based sources, averaging 1-2 Neurodes per
run and doubling as a good early-Deimos objective.

## Mid & late game

Once a squad is running Steel Path, **Circulus** on Lua is one of the most
popular full-squad farms in the game: it's a Void Fissure Survival with dense
Sentient and Corpus spawns that drops Neurodes alongside Rubedo, Ferrite, and
relics, so it's easy to find a public group for it. Because this farm is enemy
drops rather than containers, Resourceful Retriever and Resource Drop Boosters
meaningfully increase yield here.

**Plato** on Lua (Exterminate) is a solid alternative for a coordinated squad —
it guarantees a Sentient spawn within the first couple of minutes — if Circulus
matchmaking is slow.

